 <exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Our Mathematics in Democracy classes are voting on where to take a math field trip. The options are:
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The mudflats of Egypt, birthplace of geometry
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Athens, cradle of logical thought
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Moose Lake Credit Union, dispenser of mortgages
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Königsberg, for a walking tour of the bridges
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Papa John’s Pizza, home of yummy garlic sauce
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            The preference table is the following.
        </p>
        <table>
            <title></title>
            <tabular top="medium" bottom="minor" right="minor" left="minor">
                <row>
                    <cell halign="center"></cell>
                    <cell halign="center" colspan="6"># of Ballots</cell>
